node.text: Yess the electrical whisk made all the difference 😻😻😻
Tried this afew times. But still can’t the sticky texture. I wonder what went wrong. The method or ingredients? 🤔 😢

So- As you can see, I've gotten on the Dalgona bandwagon to check out the hype.
.
What's the verdict? I highly recommend an electrical whisk, if you don't have one, prepare to have an arm sore-ingly good time.
.
Is the effort worth it?  Yeh sure, once in a while but I can't imagine myself putting in this much work every morning for a cup of coffee.

I liked it alot though. It was nice, light & frothy with a hint of bitterness & I really enjoyed it! So, if you've got some spare time (who doesn't nowadays?), you should try making some Dalgona coffee too! 🌚
.
#dalgonacoffeesg #circuitbreakersg #leicasg #leicacl #leica35summilux #stayhomesg #stayhomeforsg
@foodmakescalhappy Indeed. Too time consuming for everyday. 🤣
Haha ya once in a while is ok 😆
@i_s_ky 🤣🤣 Not sure if it’ll survive the trip.
@steam.hyperpolyglot Thanks thanks! Heh, glad to hear that. 😆
Hey babe!! NICEE!! You make it look really tasty. 😋🤤
@love.life.love.unicorn How much coffee did you put in it? 😲
@so.gelly same as you! Haha 2 tablespoons. How long did you whisk it for btw?
I tried it too! But it was so strong. I gotta use less coffee
@frootlupe 🤣🤣 Hmmmm wonder if I should give it a try. 🤔
With that consistency you could spread it on toast and it'd still be awesome. 😉
Wwwooooooooow!!! Stunniiiiiiiiing capture, simply perfect timing... #staysafe Wishing you a lovely time alwaaaaays!
Omg ur dalgona looks really solid! 💯 foam on point 🤩😍
Yess the electrical whisk made all the difference 😻😻😻
Tried this afew times. But still can’t the sticky texture. I wonder what went wrong. The method or ingredients? 🤔 😢
